------------------------------------------------------<br>
After the major patch on Wednesday cross-server chatting is now possible.  This allows you to send tells either to a channel or directly to another character on another server.<br>
<br>
To join a channel on another server simply add the server name to the beginning of the channel name and a dot betweeen them.  For instance, /join povar.auction will join you to the server-wide auction channel on Povar.<br>
<br>
You can also send direct tells by using a semicolon (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  at the start of the line instead of slash (/).  So to send a tell to Baelish on the Povar server you would type <br>
<br>
&quot;;tell povar.baelish Hiya!&quot; <br>
<br>
We have confirmed with Scott Hartsman that this was an intentional feature introduced and that it will be staying in game.  Here's what he had to say:<br>
<br>
Cross Server chat is something that was done intentionally - At no small amount of work for both our development and ops teams, for that matter. <br>
<br>
<br>
The reason that it wasn't announced is because in order to allow this, we had to change around the chat systems quite a bit. We needed a few days of measuring what would happen with existing channel chat under the new arrangement as a proof of concept. <br>
<br>
<br>
If that blew up before anyone was chatting globally, we'd have known that we had more work to do. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
The other reason that it wasn't advertised yet -- As it stands, people have the ability to spam (and in some cases, are spamming) cross-server without any of the standard in-game repercussions. (i.e. If you're a jerk: I won't group with you, my guild won't help you, etc.) That definitely wasn't part of the plan, and we'd hoped to have that addressed before it was released. <br>
<br>
<br>
Over the next few days, we'll be adding more controls that allow people to keep their channels and private messages local to their servers, among other things. <br>
<br>
<br>
Best, <br>
<br>
<br>
- Scott <br>
<br>
We have had reports that a number of players have been suspended for spamming other channels with this system so it's probably advisable to use it sensibly if you want to keep an active account.<br>
